    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>stock </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce starts to thicken</p><p>Chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped fish </strong>to the sauce and give everything a good mix up, then set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>fish & leek filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter,</strong> a splash of <strong>milk and </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Transfer the <strong>fish & leek filling </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>mashed potato </strong>and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until the fish is cooked through and the top is golden \u2013 this <strong>creamy fish & leek pie</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>While the pie is cooking, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a heat proof bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 20-30 sec or until the butter has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic & parsley butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pie is nearly cooked, add your <strong>garden veg mix</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiling water</strong> (just enough to cover them) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-cod-and-leek-pie-with-garlic-and-parsley-butter-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy fish & leek pie</strong> with the <strong>garden veg mix </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>garlic & parsley butter</strong> over the top of the pie</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave off the garlic & parsley butter or just add a little!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
